===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – resembles an open mouth.

In the oracle bone script, radical {{lang|zh|口}} is used for characters having abstract meanings. Such a character can have a figurative meaning derived from the phonetic part, e.g. {{och-l|右|right}} = {{och-l|又|right hand}} + {{lang|zh|口}} and {{och-l|𪪺|strong; powerful}} = {{och-l|弓|bow}} + {{lang|zh|口}}, or be an unrelated borrowing, e.g. {{och-l|否|no}} = {{och-l|不|calyx}} + {{lang|zh|口}}.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ku(w)||mouth}}. Cognate with {{cog|grt|ku'-sik||mouth}}, {{cog|txg|𗋈|tr=ngu²|t=mouth}}.

